  "display_name": "Conflict of Laws and Jurisdiction",
  "description": "This cluster of papers explores the impact and implications of private international law within the context of the European Union. It covers a wide range of topics such as jurisdiction agreements, succession regulation, cross-border litigation, family law, choice of law, and the Brussels Regulation. The papers discuss the challenges and opportunities for legal harmonization in the EU.",
